1) Download and add it to the html file
2) jquery(selector)
	Jquery does many things without using id by simly calling library functions
3) Syntax: Jquery methods
	jquery('what to find').someAction;
	# -> represents ID 
	. -> class
	Some methods like .addclass, .removeclass, .toggleclass (which means if class is not their then add it if it is their then remove it.)
4) Jquery is more about accurate, more flexible, more choices, can make our code shorter
	Jquery represents in $ sign($ -> alias for jquery)
	eg:
	a) jQuery("li").addClass("highlight");
	b) jquery("p:contains('packages')").addClass("highlight");
	c) fadeOut
		 $("p").click(function(){
			$("this").fadeOut(2000);
		 });
	d) $(document).ready(function{
		 $('#pageID').click(function(){
	 		$('#pageID').text("the dom is fully loaded");
	 	 	});
	 	 });
JQUERY EFFECTS
http://www.w3schools.com/jquery
1) hide/show
2) fade
3) slide
4) animate
5) stop : used to stop any animation, fading and including animation
6) chaining: allows u to run multiple jquery commands one after the other
7) 	get, set(playing important role) we can set values, text when event raised
8) add
	append(), prepend